body:
struct assignment pattern of `struct_s = '{ a: '0, default:'1}` is not supported.

## example

```systemverilog
module test();

  typedef struct packed {
    logic a;
    logic b;
  } struct_t;

  struct_t s;

  assign s = '{
    a: '1,
    default: '0
  };

  initial begin
    #5 $display(s);
  end

endmodule
```

## error

```
iverilog -g2012 test.sv 
test.sv:11: syntax error
test.sv:10: error: syntax error in continuous assignment
```

